DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       _L_3_t_o_l  converts a list of _n three-byte integers packed into a character
       string pointed to by _c_p into a list of long integers pointed to by _l_p.

       _L_t_o_l_3 performs the inverse conversion from long integers	(_l_p) to	three-
       byte integers (_c_p).

       These functions are useful for file-system maintenance under 2BSD where
       disk addresses within inodes are	three bytes long.

